"title": "6648: expiation",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6648: expiation",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The removal of the guilt of sin in God's sight by the offering of a vicarious sacrifice which, in its death, bears the sin of the individual or nation concerned.</p>\n<h2>Expiation is necessary because sin is punishable by God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:30\">EXO 32:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num16:46-Num16:48\">NUM 16:46–16:48</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut21:8\">DEU 21:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps79:8-Ps79:9\">PSA 79:8–79:9</a></p>\n<h2>Expiation and the sacrificial system</h2>\n<h3>Unintentional sins expiated by the sin offering</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:1-Lev5:6\">LEV 4:1–5:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:22-Num15:29\">NUM 15:22–15:29</a></p>\n<h3>Unintentional sins requiring restitution expiated by the guilt offering</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev5:14-Lev6:7\">LEV 5:14–6:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:20-Lev19:22\">LEV 19:20–19:22</a></p>\n<h3>The nation's sins expiated on the annual Day of Atonement</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:10\">EXO 30:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:3-Lev16:34\">LEV 16:3–16:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:7\">HEB 9:7</a></p>\n<h3>Blood as a symbol of substitutionary sacrifice</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev17:11\">LEV 17:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek45:19-Ezek45:20\">EZK 45:19–45:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:22\">HEB 9:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:11\">HEB 13:11</a></p>\n<h3>The rite of expiation administered by the priests</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev9:7\">LEV 9:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev7:7\">LEV 7:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev9:15\">LEV 9:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev10:17-Lev10:18\">LEV 10:17–10:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:11\">NUM 6:11</a></p>\n<h3>Expiation and special provision for the poor</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev12:7-Lev12:8\">LEV 12:7–12:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev5:7-Lev5:13\">LEV 5:7–5:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:21-Lev14:32\">LEV 14:21–14:32</a></p>\n<h2>The sin offering as a constant reminder of the need for expiation</h2>\n<h3>Sin offerings for occasions of dedication</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:31-Exod29:33\">EXO 29:31–29:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:14-Lev8:15\">LEV 8:14–8:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num8:12\">NUM 8:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr29:21-2Chr29:24\">2CH 29:21–29:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra6:17\">EZR 6:17</a></p>\n<h3>Sin offerings for occasions of purification</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev12:6-Lev12:7\">LEV 12:6–12:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:19-Lev14:20\">LEV 14:19–14:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:49-Lev14:53\">LEV 14:49–14:53</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev15:13-Lev15:15\">LEV 15:13–15:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev15:28-Lev15:30\">LEV 15:28–15:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:1-Num19:13\">NUM 19:1–19:13</a></p>\n<h3>Sin offerings as part of the regular cycle of worship</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num28:15\">NUM 28:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num28:22\">NUM 28:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num28:30\">NUM 28:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num29:5\">NUM 29:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num29:11\">NUM 29:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num29:16\">NUM 29:16</a></p>\n<h2>The death of Jesus Christ as the fulfilment and replacement of the old sacrificial system</h2>\n<h3>The death of Jesus Christ as a substitutionary, expiatory sacrifice</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:2\">1JN 2:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:3\">1CO 15:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:4\">GAL 1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:3\">HEB 1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:18\">1PE 3:18</a></p>\n<h3>God's provision of Jesus Christ as an atoning sacrice</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:25\">ROM 3:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:10\">ISA 53:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:3\">ROM 8:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:10\">1JN 4:10</a></p>\n<h3>The blood of Jesus Christ as an atonement for sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:13-Heb9:14\">HEB 9:13–9:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:28\">MAT 26:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:7\">EPH 1:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:7\">1JN 1:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:5\">REV 1:5</a></p>\n<h3>The sacrifice of Jesus Christ as final and unique</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:27\">HEB 7:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:10\">ROM 6:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:25-Heb10:14\">HEB 9:25–10:14</a></p>",
